        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 9:50AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 950 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
East Berwick, or near Berwick, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 25 to 35 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hazleton, Berwick, Nanticoke, West Hazleton, Freeland, Bear Creek,
Dorrance, Conyngham, Nescopeck, and Slocum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
